snippet: Hong Kong customs officials seized an illegal shipment of ivory tusks, rhino horns and leopard skins worth more than $5 million, officials said Wednesday.
abstract: Hong Kong customs officials seize illegal shipment of ivory tusks, rhino horns and leopard skins worth more than $5 million; haul is second seizure of endangered species parts in a month in the city.
lead_paragraph: Hong Kong customs officials seized an illegal shipment of ivory tusks, rhino horns and leopard skins worth more than $5 million, officials said Wednesday.

headline.main: Hong Kong: Cache of Ivory Is Seized
headline.print_headline: Hong Kong: Cache of Ivory Is Seized
